
#|

not a particularly special macro, but this is being moved to it's own file
to test the suppostion that oaklisp can't compile files with internal references
to internally defined macros. personally I think it should be able to, but wtfdik

|#

(define-syntax (until test . body)
  `(labels ((fn (lambda ()
	       ,@body
	       (if ,test #t (fn)))))
     (fn)))

